# Model source configuration for model_loader.py
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# model_loader.py resolves the TensorFlow SavedModel in this order:
#   1. Local  ./saved_model/  (produced by `python train.py`) — no token needed.
#   2. HuggingFace Hub fallback — only used if ./saved_model/ is empty AND
#      HF_MODEL_REPO_ID is set below.
#
# For the normal local workflow (train it yourself), you do NOT need either
# variable — just run data_prep.py + train.py and ./saved_model/ is created.
#
# Optional: pull a pre-trained SavedModel from a HuggingFace Hub repo instead.
# HF_MODEL_REPO_ID=your-username/your-model-repo
# HF_TOKEN=hf_your_token_here   # only if that repo is private
